<p id="notice"><%= notice %></p>

<p>
  <strong>Make:</strong>
  <%= @car.make.name %>   <!--.name was added to display the name of the make on Car creation-->
</p>

<p>
  <strong>Model:</strong>
  <%= @car.model %>
</p>

<!-- Part does not currently exist in the car form, as the relationship was
added after the auto-generated code of the scaffolds, so the following block was
added to have the Part objects load from the parts table.
Citation: From PPP 03ActiveRecord, slide 39-->
<p>
  <strong>Parts:</strong>
</p>
  <ul>
      <% @car.parts.each do |part| %>
        <li><%= part.name %></li>
      <% end %>
  </ul>

  

<p>
  <strong>Vin:</strong>
  <%= @car.vin %>
</p>

<%= link_to 'Edit', edit_car_path(@car) %> |
<%= link_to 'Back', cars_path %>
